  "prompt": "How should I fill my first name and last name in a form, when I have my surname as first name in India?",
  "response": "In India, it is common for the surname to be used as a first name in some cultural contexts. However, when filling out a form, especially one that follows a standard format requiring a first name (given name) and last name (family name or surname), you should still adhere to the form's instructions for clarity and consistency.\n\n1. **First Name**: Fill in your given name (the name you are known by on a daily basis).\n2. **Last Name**: Fill in your surname (family name).\n\nFor example, if your full name is \"Rao Kumar\" and \"Rao\" is your surname while \"Kumar\" is your given name:\n\n- **First Name**: Kumar\n- **Last Name**: Rao\n\nThis will ensure that your name is correctly recorded according to international standards and helps avoid any confusion in documentation, especially if the form may be used or reviewed by people outside of India.\n\nIf the form specifically asks for \"Surname\" followed by \"First Name\" and explicitly mentions the format, you can still follow the general guidelines above for clarity. If you encounter forms that seem ambiguous, you can usually find accompanying instructions or help text to guide you, or you can reach out to the organization or person who provided the form for clarification.",
